an texts. What emerges from this is a new glimpse of the intertextuality of Day One that provides insight into the complexity of the intertextuality of a biblical text and the role that language plays in intertextuality and interpretation. In addition to the methodological insights that this approach provides to the history of interpretation, the study also sheds light on textual and theological questions that relate to Day One, including the genesis of creatio ex nihilo.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristian literature, EarlyxHistory and criticism. 0aIntertextuality in the Bible. 0aIntertextuality. 0aJewish religious literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aGenesis. 4aHermeneutik. 4aInterpretation. 4aIntertextualität. 4aSchöpfung. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh  aCreation.  aGenesis.  aHermeneutics.  aInterpretation.  aIntertextuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2009z9783110219494oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311022433740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022434440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110224344423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783